  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I noticed this during testing and I raise it for consideration.\r\n\r\nConsider the genesis hash is `0x42 * 32` and we're at slot `GENESIS_SLOT + 1`.\r\n\r\n- `state.current_justified_root == 0x00 * 32`\r\n- `get_block_root(state, get_epoch_start_slot(state.current_justified_epoch)) == 0x42 * 32`\r\n\r\nThere are two, seemingly valid ways to read the `current_justified_root` and they return different values.",
